9
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,906
There were special seats for the believers

10
00:00:38,931 --> 00:00:40,990
They sat on them

11
00:00:41,297 --> 00:00:46,844
And that main altar where rituals and celebrations were held

12
00:00:47,209 --> 00:00:52,547
Armenian celebrations have their own distinctive character

13
00:00:52,572 --> 00:00:56,766
They are held in the Armenian language

14
00:00:56,791 --> 00:00:59,474
Unlike other Christian denominations

15
00:00:59,499 --> 00:01:03,927
Which hold their celebrations in Syriac

16
00:01:03,952 --> 00:01:07,521
Or in Arabic so that others can understand

17
00:01:07,651 --> 00:01:12,964
But the Armenian church celebrations were held in Armenian

18
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:17,730
And always focused on much of what is in the Gospel

19
00:01:17,755 --> 00:01:21,984
Stories of the Nativity and the Resurrection

20
00:01:22,818 --> 00:01:25,448
The celebrations, for example Christmas

21
00:01:25,473 --> 00:01:29,953
Or the commemoration of the Armenian genocide on April 15

22
00:01:29,978 --> 00:01:35,552
Or Easter, which usually falls in April every year
